==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Effigiate
<hw>Ef*fig"i*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>effigiatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>effigiare</ets> to form, fr.
<ets>effigies</ets>. See <er>Effigy</er>.]</ety> <def>To form as an
effigy; hence, to fashion; to adapt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[He must] <qex>effigiate</qex> and conform himself to those
circumstances.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effigiation</ent>⟦br⟧
